We are in the process of cleaning the wound, but we need an investigative unit intended only for Montreal, as well as supervision to prevent a return of questionable practices.
How to clean up.
Regularly.
Jacques Duchesneau, for his part, notes that "officials have stolen several hundred million dollars", but he is particularly concerned about the role of "mandates who are informed about tactics" when they were not involved in the fraud!
Based on a 70% share of black money in the financing of the Quebec election campaigns, he jokes: "I was told that this was only a weak slap in the face of reality."
The Quebec government proposes to limit the donations to parties to $100, which according to him would not change the situation: "Until campaign spending is strictly limited, black money will be circulating in politics."
