The goods in the Walmart stores are on average between 8 and 27% cheaper than in large supermarkets.
This is why many of the slightly paid Walmart employees buy only at their own workplace.
The prices and the product range made Walmart one of the largest companies in the USA.
According to critics, Walmart can often sell the goods so cheaply only because the employees are poorly paid.
The latter also complain about heavy working conditions, for example missing forklifts or hand scanners.
The protesters at "Black Friday" demanded wage increases and expressed their anger at the fact that the contribution for the company's health insurance had increased from 30 to 100 dollars a month.
