If Walmart were to completely convert the wage increases to the customers, every purchase would cost them only 46 cents more in the future.
That would be $12.39 a year for them compared to today.
Proponents of Walmart are satisfied that only nine states have protested and that they have not caused any loss to the company.
The Black Friday lasted the next day in its store from 8 pm on Thursday to midnight, and during this period Walmart sold about 5000 items per second.
In total, the Walmart cash registers carried out nearly 100 million transactions on "Black Friday".
