The austerity measures of virtually all EU southern states will undoubtedly lead to the same situation in which people are forced to emigrate (as was the case in the 19th century) under the pressure of a catastrophic crash of their social level, or to pay for a hunger wage on the fringes of society, hoping that private investment capital will eventually flow into the country.
