If it comes from another EU country, only poverty moves from one country to another; or capital remains the same, because in China, India, Brazil, Turkey, Morocco, Egypt, or Africa, the workers work for a fraction of European wages.
This concerns the whole of Latin America.
Liberal theories and media claim to the extent that the state is not allowed to participate in its own economy with capital, and that planned economy leads to economic catastrophe.
Private capital insists closely on its position that the state must not intervene in the economy as a directing factor.
But then you have to ask yourself whether private capital does not influence or even direct politics and thus the entire state in its own selfish sense.
Here is the clear answer: Yes.
The proof of this is the existence of a virtually all-powerful lobby that is ubiquitous in all countries.
The result is a desperate situation in the area of corruption, mutual predation, legislation in which virtually everything is burdensome, but nothing criminal.
